      The box
   =20
 =20

There is so much, but I want to start with Serum.
If a troubled company has a few days to beg potential investors for a bailo=
ut before it files for bankruptcy, and it sends those investors its balance=
 sheet so they can consider investing, and they all pass, and then the comp=
any files for bankruptcy, of course the balance sheet was=C2=A0bad. That is=
 not a state of affairs that is consistent with a pristine fortress balance=
 sheet.
But there is a range of possible badness, even in bankruptcy, and the balan=
ce sheet that Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s failed crypto exchange FTX.com se=
nt to potential investors last week before filing for bankruptcy on Friday =
is very bad. It=E2=80=99s=C2=A0an Excel file full of the howling of ghosts =
and the shrieking of tortured souls. If you look too long at that spreadshe=
et,=C2=A0you will go insane. Antoine Gara, Kadhim Shubber and Joshua Oliver=
 at the Financial Times=C2=A0reported on Saturday:

Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s main international FTX exchange held just $900m=
n in easily sellable assets against $9bn of liabilities the day before it c=
ollapsed into bankruptcy, according to investment materials seen by the Fin=
ancial Times.
The largest portion of those liquid assets listed on a FTX international ba=
lance sheet dated Thursday was $470mn of Robinhood shares owned by a Bankma=
n-Fried vehicle not listed in Friday=E2=80=99s bankruptcy filing, which inc=
luded 134 corporate entities.

Seems bad, but it somehow keeps getting worse:
A spreadsheet listing FTX international=E2=80=99s assets and liabilities, s=
een by the Financial Times, point at the issues that brought Bankman-Fried =
crashing back down to earth. It references $5bn of withdrawals last Sunday,=
 and a negative $8bn entry described as =E2=80=9Chidden, poorly internally =
labled =E2=80=98fiat@=E2=80=99 account=E2=80=9D.
What.
The vast majority of FTX Trading=E2=80=99s recorded assets are either illiq=
uid venture capital investments or crypto tokens that are not widely traded=
, according to the spreadsheet, which cautions that the figures =E2=80=9Car=
e rough values, and could be slightly off; there is also obviously a chance=
 of typos etc. They also change a bit over time as trades happen.=E2=80=9D
What.
In all, the spreadsheet says FTX Trading=E2=80=99s assets were $900mn of =
=E2=80=9Cliquid=E2=80=9D assets, $5.5bn of =E2=80=9Cless liquid=E2=80=9D as=
sets consisting of crypto tokens, and $3.2bn of illiquid private equity inv=
estments. There is also an obscure $7mn holding called =E2=80=9CTRUMPLOSE=
=E2=80=9D. There are no bitcoin assets listed, despite bitcoin liabilities =
of $1.4bn.
What. And yet bad as all of this is, it can=E2=80=99t prepare you for the b=
alance sheet itself,  published by FT Alphaville, which is less a balance s=
heet and more a list of some tickers interspersed with hasty apologies. If =
you blithely add up the =E2=80=9Cliquid,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cless liquid=E2=
=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cilliquid=E2=80=9D assets, at their =E2=80=9Cdeliverable=
=E2=80=9D value as of Thursday, and subtract the liabilities, you do get a =
positive net equity of about $700 million. (Roughly $9.6 billion of assets =
versus $8.9 billion of liabilities.) But then there is the =E2=80=9CHidden,=
 poorly internally labeled =E2=80=98fiat@=E2=80=99 account,=E2=80=9D with a=
 balance of negative $8 billion.
  [1]
=C2=A0I don=E2=80=99t actually think that you=E2=80=99re supposed to subtra=
ct that number from net equity =E2=80=94 though I do not know how this bala=
nce sheet is supposed to work! =E2=80=94 but it doesn=E2=80=99t matter. If =
you try to calculate the equity of a balance sheet with an entry for HIDDEN=
 POORLY INTERNALLY LABELED ACCOUNT, Microsoft Clippy will appear before you=
 in the flesh, bloodshot and staggering, with a knife in his little paper-c=
lip hand, saying =E2=80=9Cjust what do you think you=E2=80=99re doing=C2=A0=
Dave?=E2=80=9D You cannot apply ordinary arithmetic to numbers in a cell la=
beled =E2=80=9CHIDDEN POORLY INTERNALLY LABELED ACCOUNT.=E2=80=9D The resul=
t of adding or subtracting those numbers with ordinary numbers is not a num=
ber; it is prison.
  [2]

But here is the paragraph that drove me=C2=A0insane:
The company=E2=80=99s biggest asset as of Thursday was $2.2bn worth of a cr=
yptocurrency called Serum. Serum=E2=80=99s market value was $88mn on Saturd=
ay, according to data provider CryptoCompare, suggesting FTX=E2=80=99s hold=
ings would be worth far less if sold into the market. CryptoCompare=E2=80=
=99s figures take into account the coin=E2=80=99s liquidity.
If you look on the balance sheet, that=E2=80=99s the biggest =E2=80=9Cdeliv=
erable=E2=80=9D number: $2,187,876,172 of SRM, the ticker for the Serum tok=
en, down from $5,430,110,335 =E2=80=9Cbefore this week.=E2=80=9D (=E2=80=9C=
Before this week=E2=80=9D means, of course, before=C2=A0last=C2=A0week =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0before the week that FTX was circulating this spreadsheet =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0and I will use it as a shorthand to mean roughly =E2=80=9Cbefor=
e Nov. 8.=E2=80=9D On Nov. 8, the trouble at FTX became public, and everyth=
ing FTX-related crashed.)
As of about 11 a.m. today,  CoinMarketCap showed the Serum token having a p=
rice of $0.25,=C2=A0a =E2=80=9Cmarket cap=E2=80=9D of about $65 million and=
 a =E2=80=9Cfully diluted market cap=E2=80=9D of about $2.5 billion. Those =
numbers would have been a bit higher =E2=80=94=C2=A0say $0.35 to $0.40 per =
token =E2=80=94 on Thursday, when this balance sheet was created. The price=
 crashed last Tuesday, during FTX=E2=80=99s death throes; before that the t=
oken=C2=A0traded around $0.80. In round numbers FTX probably held something=
 like two-thirds of Serum=E2=80=99s fully diluted market cap, and roughly 2=
0 times its basic market cap.
In crypto, market cap is (as CoinMarketCap puts it) =E2=80=9Cthe total mark=
et value of a cryptocurrency's circulating supply =E2=80=A6=C2=A0analogous =
to the free-float capitalization in the stock market,=E2=80=9D while fully =
diluted market cap is =E2=80=9Cthe market cap if the max supply was in circ=
